File: platform/cli/src/commands/start.ts lines 81-89.

Current code:
```typescript
const isPortInUse = (port: number): Promise<boolean> =>
  new Promise(resolve => {
    const server = net.createServer();
    server.once('error', () => resolve(true));
    server.once('listening', () => {
      server.close(() => resolve(false));
    });
    server.listen(port, '127.0.0.1');
  });
```

Fix: Change the error handler to inspect the error code:
```typescript
server.once('error', (err: NodeJS.ErrnoException) => {
  server.close();
  if (err.code === 'EADDRINUSE') {
    resolve(true);
  } else {
    reject(err);
  }
});
```

Then in the caller (the start command), catch the rejection and handle EACCES specifically with a user-friendly message like 'Permission denied: port N requires elevated privileges'. Other errors can use a generic 'Failed to check port N: <error message>'.

Also update the Promise constructor from `new Promise(resolve => ...)` to `new Promise<boolean>((resolve, reject) => ...)` since we now need reject.
